1.List the emps who joined in January and Fabruary in 1981.
 
ANS:- SELECT*FROM EMP WHERE HIREDATE BETWEEN '01-JAN-1981' AND '28-FEB-1981'

2.List all the emps except ‘PRESIDENT’ & ‘MANAGER” in asc order of Salaries. 

ANS:- SELECT*FROM EMP WHERE JOB IN('PRESIDENT','MANAGER') ORDER BY SAL ASC

3.Display all the details oif the employees where the 2nd last character of the name is K and which length is 5.

ANS:- SELECT*FROM EMP WHERE LENGTH(ENAME)=5 AND  ENAME LIKE ('%K_')

4.List the emps where  third character of their name must be ‘r’ and job is start with M or A.

ANS:- SELECT*FROM EMP WHERE  ENAME LIKE ('__R%') AND (JOB LIKE('M') OR JOB LIKE('A%'))

5.Show all the employees name and job in lowe case.

ANS:- SELECT LOWER(ENAME),LOWER(JOB) FROM EMP

6.List the emps whose Jobs are same as ALLEN.

ANS:- SELECT*FROM EMP WHERE JOB=(SELECT JOB FROM EMP WHERE ENAME='ALLEN')

7.Display department-wise total salaries for all the Managers and Analysts, only if the average salaries for the same is greater than or equal to 3000.

ANS:- SELECT SUM(SAL) FROM EMP WHERE JOB IN('MANAGER','ANALYST') GROUP BY DEPTNO HAVING AVG(SAL)>=3000

8.Display all the employees who are getting some commission in department 20 & 30

ANS:- SELECT*FROM EMP WHERE COMM IS NOT NULL AND DEPTNO IN (20,30)

9.Select details of all the employees working for FORD.

ANS:- SELECT*FROM EMP WHERE MGR=(SELECT EMPNO FROM EMP WHERE  ENAME='FORD')

10.Find out the job wise no. of Analysty and Clerk whose salary is more than 800.

ANS:- SELECT JOB,COUNT(*) FROM EMP WHERE SAL>800 GROUP BY JOB HAVING JOB IN('ANALYST','CLERK')

11.Find out the department where more than 3 emplyees are working.

ANS:-SELECT DEPTNO,COUNT(*)FROM EMP  GROUP BY DEPTNO HAVING COUNT(*)>3

12.Show the unique department no from the emp table.

ANS:- SELECT DISTINCT DEPTNO FROM EMP

13.Increase the salary to 5% for the Analysts who joined in 1982. 

ANS:-  UPDATE EMP SET SAL=SAL+SAL*0.05 WHERE HIREDATE BETWEEN '01-JAN-82' AND '31-DEC-82'

14.Rename the column name from mgr to reporing_boss. [After completing the task rename it again reporting_boss to mgr.]

ANS:- ALTER TABLE EMP RENAME COLUMN MGR TO REPORTING_BOSS;
      ALTER TABLE EMP RENAME COLUME REPORTING_BOSS TO MGR
	  
15.Delete those employees who get commission as well as whose salary is greater than 1800.

ANS:- DELETE FROM EMP WHERE SAL>1800 AND COMM IS NOT NULL

16.Display job-wise maximum salary, minimum salary and average salary in a single query.

ANS:- SELECT JOB,MAX(SAL),MIN(SAL),AVG(SAL) FROM EMP GROUP BY JOB





